any universities to offer courses on "Psychology of Sustainability." This book is the perfect text to provide an introduction to the subject. Throughout the book, readers will find new ways of framing questions related to human adaptability and evolutionary psychology. Psychology of Sustainability is ideal for students or professionals who are looking to contribute to the conversation"--</subfield><subfield code="c">Provided by publisher.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="596"><subfield code="a">29</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Environmental psychology.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2="0" tag="650"><subfield code="a">Sustainability</subfield><subfield code="x">Psychological aspects.</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="949"><subfield code="a">BF353.5 .S87 J66 2015</subfield><subfield code="h">GMCT-OS-B</subfield><subfield code="i">1007422114</subfield><subfield code="p">204.65</subfield><subfield code="k">AVAIL_SOON</subfield></datafield><datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="926"><subfield code="a">BF353.5 .S87 J66 2015</subfield><subfield code="w">LC</subfield><subfield code="c">1</subfield><subfield code="i">1007422114</subfield><subfield code="d">4/14/2016</subfield><subfield code="e">4/11/2016</subfield><subfield code="l">ON_SHELF</subfield><subfield code="m">GR_MACEWAN</subfield><subfield code="n">3</subfield><subfield code="p">$194.90</subfield><subfield code="r">Y</subfield><subfield code="s">Y</subfield><subfield code="t">BOOK</subfield><subfield code="u">10/16/2014</subfield></datafield></record>